      QA('What is a Trial Balance?',
          'Trial balance is a statement of debit and credit balances (or totals) of all ledger accounts on a particular date, prepared to test the arithmetical accuracy of the books. The two columns must agree.'),
      QA('What is a Bank Reconciliation Statement (BRS)?',
          'BRS is a statement prepared to reconcile (match) the difference between the bank balance shown by the cash book and the pass book on a particular date, by listing the causes of difference like unpresented cheques and bank charges.'),
